answers.answer: Have you been to the doctor? Sudden migraines are a sign of preeclampsia and not something to be taken lightly. If you haven't talked to your doctor you really should.
I agree with glittergirl, definitely get it checked out!

question: I have been having bad migraine for the past few days.  Taking tylenol religiously and it's not working.  36 weeks with my fourth, so I have 3 at home that I need to be able to function for.  Any advice on what else I may take??
